record.title: COMMITTEE ON RULES AND ADMINISTRATION RULES OF PROCEDURE

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that pursuant to paragraph 2 of rule XXVI of the Standing Rules of the Senate, the Rules of Procedure of the Committee on Rules and Administration, adopted on January 31, 2007, be printed in the Record.

record.narrative: There being no objection, the material was ordered to be printed in the RECORD, as follows:
